W-why did he go back there?

518
00:29:17.113 --> 00:29:18.395
I don't know.

519
00:29:18.447 --> 00:29:19.647
Said he had
lingering suspicions.

520
00:29:19.699 --> 00:29:20.748
Couldn't sleep.

521
00:29:20.783 --> 00:29:22.149
About Alison?

522
00:29:22.201 --> 00:29:24.151
I did some research
a few weeks back.

523
00:29:24.203 --> 00:29:27.238
and something came up which
I was hoping. I was praying

524
00:29:27.290 --> 00:29:29.156
I wouldn't have to share
with you.

525
00:29:29.158 --> 00:29:32.243
but it doesn't look like
we have that option anymore.

526
00:29:34.630 --> 00:29:36.914
What is this?

527
00:29:39.335 --> 00:29:41.252
It's a DNA report.

528
00:29:41.304 --> 00:29:44.438
I had a sample
of Joanie's DNA analyzed.

529
00:29:44.473 --> 00:29:46.640
You're not her father.

530
00:29:46.676 --> 00:29:49.043
I'm sorry to have
to tell you that.

531
00:29:53.516 --> 00:29:55.849
I know that. Jon.

532
00:29:55.851 --> 00:29:56.850
What?

533
00:29:56.902 --> 00:29:58.953
Y-you...
you know?

534
00:29:58.988 --> 00:30:00.104
Why is this relevant?

535
00:30:03.659 --> 00:30:06.493
Well. uh...

536
00:30:06.529 --> 00:30:08.495
...I also have a video
of an altercation

537
00:30:08.531 --> 00:30:11.498
between Scotty and Alison
taken outside The Lobster Roll

538
00:30:11.534 --> 00:30:13.567
the night that Scott
was killed.

539
00:30:13.602 --> 00:30:15.703
I have phone records
wherein it shows

540
00:30:15.755 --> 00:30:17.705
he called her multiple times
in the months

541
00:30:17.757 --> 00:30:20.507
leading up to his death.

542
00:30:20.543 --> 00:30:22.793
I suspected that. perhaps.

543
00:30:22.845 --> 00:30:24.511
Scott was Joanie's father.

544
00:30:24.547 --> 00:30:25.879
Obviously. since
the report came back.

545
00:30:25.881 --> 00:30:27.214
I realized that isn't true.

546
00:30:27.266 --> 00:30:29.049
No. It's Cole.

547
00:30:31.721 --> 00:30:33.988
Right.

548
00:30:34.023 --> 00:30:37.057
Just what the test indicated.

549
00:30:38.394 --> 00:30:40.561
So I started to formulate
a hypothesis.

550
00:30:40.613 --> 00:30:45.566
Maybe Scott knew
Cole was Joanie's father.

551
00:30:45.568 --> 00:30:47.067
Maybe he was
blackmailing her.

552
00:30:47.119 --> 00:30:49.069
Maybe she killed him
to keep him quiet.

553
00:30:49.121 --> 00:30:51.572
Come on. Jon.
that... that's...

554
00:30:51.574 --> 00:30:52.906
that's ridiculous.

555
00:30:52.958 --> 00:30:54.541
Not to me.

556
00:30:54.577 --> 00:30:57.077
I can now put her
at the site

557
00:30:57.079 --> 00:30:59.079
on the night
of the accident.

558
00:30:59.081 --> 00:31:01.582
Hey. for all we know.
they got into another fight.

559
00:31:01.584 --> 00:31:03.684
She pushed him in front
of an oncoming car.

560
00:31:03.719 --> 00:31:04.668
I don't know.

561
00:31:04.720 --> 00:31:06.220
The point is
that I believe

562
00:31:06.255 --> 00:31:08.422
we have enough evidence now

563
00:31:08.424 --> 00:31:10.257
to build reasonable doubt
in the jurors' minds.

564
00:31:10.259 --> 00:31:11.425
enough to hang 'em

565
00:31:11.477 --> 00:31:15.062
or maybe even
to get you off entirely.

566
00:31:15.097 --> 00:31:18.065
By turning the blame
on Alison?

567
00:31:18.100 --> 00:31:21.685
Noah. look. I have been
doing this a long time.

568
00:31:21.737 --> 00:31:23.737
and I usually can feel

569
00:31:23.773 --> 00:31:26.607
which way a jury is leaning
in my bones.

570
00:31:26.659 --> 00:31:30.411
I do not have a good feeling
about this.

571
00:31:30.446 --> 00:31:31.912
We're running out of time.

572
00:31:31.947 --> 00:31:33.947
This is my Hail Mary pass.

573
00:31:33.999 --> 00:31:35.949
I have to put Detective Jeffries
on the stand.

574
00:31:36.001 --> 00:31:37.918
Now. what I'm asking you

575
00:31:37.953 --> 00:31:40.721
is. do I have your permission
to do that?

576
00:31:51.800 --> 00:31:55.136
_

577
00:31:56.839 --> 00:31:58.338
No. that's too much.

578
00:31:58.374 --> 00:31:59.807
I can get them from Danny
for two bucks less.

579
00:31:59.809 --> 00:32:00.808
Not for hard backs.

580
00:32:00.810 --> 00:32:02.142
I don't need
hard backs.

581
00:32:02.144 --> 00:32:03.310
Thought you said
this was a wedding.

582
00:32:03.312 --> 00:32:04.395
No. we're making salad.

583
00:32:04.447 --> 00:32:06.063
I need soft shells and culls.

584
00:32:06.115 --> 00:32:07.898
Listen. you said wedding.

585
00:32:07.950 --> 00:32:08.899
I thought you were doing
something special.

586
00:32:08.951 --> 00:32:09.817
Excuse me.

587
00:32:09.819 --> 00:32:11.235
Okay. Paulie.
how about

588
00:32:11.287 --> 00:32:12.486
you lose the attitude

589
00:32:12.538 --> 00:32:14.421
and you just give them to me
for eight?

590
00:32:14.457 --> 00:32:16.924
You insane?
Eleven.

591
00:32:16.959 --> 00:32:17.991
No way.
Eleven?

592
00:32:17.993 --> 00:32:19.626
I can just go
to the wholesaler.

593
00:32:19.662 --> 00:32:21.628
I know for a fact that Sysco
gives them to Danny for seven.

594
00:32:21.664 --> 00:32:22.663
so eight is a good deal.

595
00:32:22.665 --> 00:32:24.331
Not for these puppies.

596
00:32:24.383 --> 00:32:26.166
These are from my secret place.
They're sweeter.

597
00:32:26.168 --> 00:32:27.968
Your "secret place"?

598
00:32:28.003 --> 00:32:30.087
Fine.
You don't believe me?

599
00:32:30.139 --> 00:32:31.338
Go to Danny.

600
00:32:31.340 --> 00:32:33.090
<i>if</i> the DEC hasn't shut him down

601
00:32:33.142 --> 00:32:34.675
for selling undersized bugs.

602
00:32:34.727 --> 00:32:36.844
You'll be lucky to get
a half a pound off him.

603
00:32:36.846 --> 00:32:40.013
but hey. knock yourself out.
sweetheart.

604
00:32:40.065 --> 00:32:42.599
Okay. nine is my final offer.

605
00:32:42.651 --> 00:32:44.351
Make it ten.
you got a deal.

606
00:32:48.023 --> 00:32:49.990
Fine. ten.

607
00:32:50.025 --> 00:32:51.859
Good to have you back.
Bailey.

608
00:32:55.247 --> 00:32:56.697
Ugh.

609
00:32:56.699 --> 00:33:00.200
Who's the douche bag
in the Bimmer?

610
00:33:07.593 --> 00:33:08.959
When's
the actual opening?

611
00:33:09.011 --> 00:33:11.044
Uh. next week.

612
00:33:11.046 --> 00:33:12.546
You guys ready?

613
00:33:12.548 --> 00:33:14.965
Yeah. I think so.

614
00:33:15.017 --> 00:33:16.383
Who's gonna
look after the place

615
00:33:16.385 --> 00:33:20.804
when you come back
to the city?

616
00:33:20.856 --> 00:33:23.357
Uh. Luisa.

617
00:33:23.392 --> 00:33:27.194
Really?
They're not taking a honeymoon?

618
00:33:27.229 --> 00:33:28.729
Actually. they've. uh...

619
00:33:28.781 --> 00:33:32.366
they've asked me to stay on
a little longer.

620
00:33:32.401 --> 00:33:34.034
What?

621
00:33:34.069 --> 00:33:36.236
Well. just until they get back
from their honeymoon.

622
00:33:36.238 --> 00:33:39.072
- How long is that?
- Uh. a few weeks.

623
00:33:39.074 --> 00:33:41.008
A few weeks?

624
00:33:41.043 --> 00:33:43.160
Um. look.

625
00:33:43.212 --> 00:33:46.747
I've been meaning
to ask you. um...

626
00:33:46.799 --> 00:33:49.333
...Cole and I have an idea

627
00:33:49.385 --> 00:33:52.853
that maybe we can keep
the restaurant open all year.

628
00:33:52.888 --> 00:33:54.755
Uh. not full-time.
of course.

629
00:33:54.757 --> 00:33:58.592
just Thursday to Sunday.

630
00:33:58.594 --> 00:34:01.261
Okay.

631
00:34:01.263 --> 00:34:02.963
What do you think of that?

632
00:34:02.998 --> 00:34:05.349
Well. as long as you're just
a silent investor.

633
00:34:05.401 --> 00:34:07.935
it makes no difference to me.

634
00:34:09.238 --> 00:34:10.187
That was the agreement.
Alison.

635
00:34:10.239 --> 00:34:11.572
Yeah. I know.

636
00:34:11.607 --> 00:34:12.773
Y-you work out here
during the summer.

637
00:34:12.825 --> 00:34:15.075
- In the fall...
- I know.

638
00:34:15.110 --> 00:34:17.544
This was never supposed to turn
into a full-time gig.

639
00:34:17.580 --> 00:34:20.214
I know.

640
00:34:23.118 --> 00:34:26.787
So what are you trying
to tell me?

641
00:34:28.791 --> 00:34:31.091
Um...

642
00:34:31.126 --> 00:34:33.293
...I like it.

643
00:34:33.295 --> 00:34:35.262
What. you like being away
from us for half the week?

644
00:34:35.297 --> 00:34:36.964
Wait. no. I...

645
00:34:36.966 --> 00:34:38.799
I like the work.

646
00:34:38.801 --> 00:34:40.551
I booked a trip to Europe
in the fall.

647
00:34:40.603 --> 00:34:41.401
Remember?

648
00:34:41.437 --> 00:34:42.386
Yeah. I know.

649
00:34:42.438 --> 00:34:43.637
and it's fine.

650
00:34:43.689 --> 00:34:45.222
You can go.

651
00:34:45.274 --> 00:34:47.074
and I'll just bring Joanie
out here with me

652
00:34:47.109 --> 00:34:49.343
and Gigi too. and...

653
00:34:49.378 --> 00:34:50.811
You know. you'd be free

654
00:34:50.813 --> 00:34:52.479
to do all the writing
you want. you...

655
00:34:54.617 --> 00:34:55.899
Uh. who is it?

656
00:34:55.951 --> 00:34:59.486
Luisa.

657
00:34:59.488 --> 00:35:01.822
Look. let's talk
about this tonight.

658
00:35:01.874 --> 00:35:03.624
Can we?

659
00:35:03.659 --> 00:35:05.259
W-we can leave as soon
as the ceremony is over

660
00:35:05.294 --> 00:35:06.460
and we can go back
to the hotel.

661
00:35:06.495 --> 00:35:07.578
- Yeah. fine. whatever.
- No.

662
00:35:07.630 --> 00:35:10.130
Look. we can...

663
00:35:12.735 --> 00:35:15.252
- I'm looking for Alison.
- She's right there.

664
00:35:15.304 --> 00:35:17.170
Hey.
Did I interrupt something?

665
00:35:17.172 --> 00:35:19.606
No. no. it's fine.

666
00:35:19.642 --> 00:35:21.174
Is it still okay
for me to change here?

667
00:35:21.226 --> 00:35:22.676
No. of course.
Come in.

668
00:35:22.678 --> 00:35:25.262
Put your stuff down here.

669
00:35:30.569 --> 00:35:32.185
Today's gonna be wonderful.
I promise.

670
00:35:32.237 --> 00:35:33.904
Thank you.

671
00:35:38.193 --> 00:35:41.111
<i>Testing.
One. two. three.</i>

672
00:35:41.163 --> 00:35:42.996
<i>Testing.</i>

673
00:35:43.032 --> 00:35:46.450
<i>One. two. three.</i>

674
00:35:49.254 --> 00:35:51.872
<i>Marco?</i>

675
00:35:51.874 --> 00:35:53.874
<i>Marco?</i>

676
00:35:53.926 --> 00:35:56.043
Polo!

677
00:36:02.618 --> 00:36:04.651
I feel kind of hot

678
00:36:04.687 --> 00:36:07.421
and itchy. like. uh...
I don't know.

679
00:36:07.456 --> 00:36:10.157
Maybe you're having cold feet?

680
00:36:10.192 --> 00:36:11.725
No. no.
No. no.

681
00:36:11.760 --> 00:36:13.310
This... this feels physical.

682
00:36:13.362 --> 00:36:16.196
like I'm coming down
with something.

683
00:36:16.231 --> 00:36:17.564
Nope.
Feel fine to me.

684
00:36:17.566 --> 00:36:19.232
No. look.

685
00:36:19.284 --> 00:36:20.150
- Ah.
- Is it red?

686
00:36:20.202 --> 00:36:21.568
No.

687
00:36:21.620 --> 00:36:23.487
Are you sure?
'Cause it feels pretty sore.

688
00:36:23.539 --> 00:36:27.240
Y-yeah. I think
you'll feel fine tomorrow.

689
00:36:28.544 --> 00:36:30.077
Is her family here yet?

690
00:36:30.129 --> 00:36:32.412
- Yeah. some of them.
- Yeah.

691
00:36:32.414 --> 00:36:34.414
There's a lot of them.

692
00:36:34.466 --> 00:36:37.501
And they expect to spend
a lot of time with us.

693
00:36:37.553 --> 00:36:40.087
Well. then it's good you're here
and not back in the city.

694
00:36:40.089 --> 00:36:42.506
You know. she can be
a little irrational.

695
00:36:42.558 --> 00:36:44.007
Not a little irrational.
I mean...

696
00:36:44.059 --> 00:36:45.759
you know. most of the time.
we're good.

697
00:36:45.811 --> 00:36:47.060
I understand where
she's coming from.

698
00:36:47.096 --> 00:36:48.679
but sometimes she is
legitimately crazy.

699
00:36:48.731 --> 00:36:49.930
- What. Luisa?
- Yeah.

700
00:36:49.932 --> 00:36:51.398
I find that hard to imagine.
Why...

701
00:36:51.433 --> 00:36:52.766
No. she says
she's affected by

702
00:36:52.818 --> 00:36:53.934
the cycles of the moon.
which I thought

703
00:36:53.936 --> 00:36:55.852
was bullshit.
but she's right.

704
00:36:55.904 --> 00:36:57.604
I mean. every full moon.
she's like...

705
00:36:57.656 --> 00:37:00.857
she's completely emotional;
she makes no sense.

706
00:37:00.909 --> 00:37:03.744
Okay. well. that's only
a few days a month.

707
00:37:11.286 --> 00:37:13.537
She can't have kids.

708
00:37:15.591 --> 00:37:17.257
Did you know that?

709
00:37:19.678 --> 00:37:21.628
No.

710
00:37:21.630 --> 00:37:23.964
I didn't.

711
00:37:23.966 --> 00:37:26.266
Yeah.

712
00:37:31.940 --> 00:37:33.306
Well.

713
00:37:33.358 --> 00:37:37.411
you have... you have talked
about it. right?

714
00:37:37.446 --> 00:37:39.896
Not really.
No.

715
00:37:39.948 --> 00:37:41.615
We talked...

716
00:37:41.650 --> 00:37:42.816
...around it.

717
00:37:42.818 --> 00:37:45.285
You know. maybe...

718
00:37:45.320 --> 00:37:46.920
...adopt in a couple years.

719
00:37:46.955 --> 00:37:48.488
which...

720
00:37:48.490 --> 00:37:51.458
...I said I was cool with.
but...

721
00:37:55.130 --> 00:37:56.630
I think I always thought

722
00:37:56.665 --> 00:37:59.499
I was gonna get to be
a father again...

723
00:38:01.053 --> 00:38:03.336
...and I'd get another shot
to be a dad

724
00:38:03.338 --> 00:38:06.673
and not fuck it up this time.

725
00:38:06.708 --> 00:38:10.477
to be more...

726
00:38:10.512 --> 00:38:13.013
...careful.

727
00:38:26.195 --> 00:38:28.195
Cole. I...

728
00:38:28.247 --> 00:38:30.831
Do you love her?

729
00:38:30.866 --> 00:38:32.299
- Yes.
- Are you sure?

730
00:38:32.334 --> 00:38:34.117
Oh. yeah.
Yeah. yeah.

731
00:38:36.255 --> 00:38:40.624
I mean. I was sure
once before too.

732
00:38:40.676 --> 00:38:42.175
Yeah. well...

733
00:38:42.211 --> 00:38:44.294
...you and I were so young.

734
00:38:44.346 --> 00:38:46.480
and we didn't know
what we were doing.

735
00:38:48.617 --> 00:38:52.853
And then we were dealt
the world's worst hand and...

736
00:38:52.888 --> 00:38:55.055
...we folded.

737
00:38:57.392 --> 00:39:00.560
But this is not
the same thing.

738
00:39:00.562 --> 00:39:01.895
You're a man now.

739
00:39:01.897 --> 00:39:03.029
You know what you want.

740
00:39:03.065 --> 00:39:05.232
and you know
how to protect it.

741
00:39:05.284 --> 00:39:08.735
Y-you can wait five. ten.
20 years

742
00:39:08.737 --> 00:39:10.036
for the perfect girl
to come along

743
00:39:10.072 --> 00:39:12.739
to give you the perfect child.
but...

744
00:39:12.791 --> 00:39:15.742
...what if she never shows up?

745
00:39:17.579 --> 00:39:22.499
This is your chance
to be happy again. Cole.

746
00:39:22.551 --> 00:39:24.084
You should take it.

747
00:39:39.234 --> 00:39:41.768
Beautiful.

748
00:39:41.820 --> 00:39:44.437
Beautiful.
You look great.

749
00:39:44.439 --> 00:39:46.356
All right. can we get
a little happy one?

750
00:39:46.408 --> 00:39:47.941
Oh. that's good.
That's great.

751
00:39:47.943 --> 00:39:50.043
That's... yep.

752
00:39:50.078 --> 00:39:52.696
All right. let's have the
wedding party come in over here.

753
00:39:52.748 --> 00:39:54.414
Come on in. ladies.

754
00:39:57.286 --> 00:39:58.919
All the family.

755
00:40:03.792 --> 00:40:06.226
All right. guys.
let's get a photo of everyone.

756
00:40:06.261 --> 00:40:08.461
- Yay.
- Yay.

757
00:40:19.808 --> 00:40:21.942
<i>♪ What's that I see? ♪</i>

758
00:40:23.445 --> 00:40:26.780
<i>♪ Is that her
on her way back home? ♪</i>

759
00:40:26.815 --> 00:40:28.949
<i>♪ Do my eyes deceive me? ♪</i>

760
00:40:31.320 --> 00:40:33.403
<i>♪ We had a falling-out
the night before ♪</i>

761
00:40:33.455 --> 00:40:36.590
<i>♪ She said she was going away ♪</i>

762
00:40:39.161 --> 00:40:42.162
<i>♪ She put on her coat.
walked through the door ♪</i>

763
00:40:42.214 --> 00:40:44.331
<i>♪ Do those eyes deceive me? ♪</i>

764
00:40:46.969 --> 00:40:50.420
<i>♪ I said please
think about... ♪</i>

765
00:40:50.472 --> 00:40:51.838
Holy shit.

766
00:40:51.840 --> 00:40:53.340
- Lockhart.
- Oh.

767
00:40:53.392 --> 00:40:56.309
- Look. it's Scott.
- Oh!

768
00:40:56.345 --> 00:40:58.278
Hey. what's up. man?

769
00:41:07.489 --> 00:41:09.189
Hey.

770
00:41:09.191 --> 00:41:11.441
I know you're busy.
but can we talk for a second?

771
00:41:11.493 --> 00:41:14.110
Uh. yeah. yeah. of course.

772
00:41:14.162 --> 00:41:17.163
<i>♪ I couldn't believe
it happened to me ♪</i>

773
00:41:17.199 --> 00:41:19.532
<i>♪ I cried like a fool ♪</i>

774
00:41:26.008 --> 00:41:28.375
Listen. I've been. uh...

775
00:41:28.427 --> 00:41:30.293
I've been thinking
about it. and. uh.

776
00:41:30.345 --> 00:41:33.046
this isn't gonna work
for me.

777
00:41:33.048 --> 00:41:34.631
Wh... what isn't gonna work?

